  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Co-ordinators, Community Enablement",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>We are seeking TWO community workers to support the execution of Game-On with CARE, a community project by CARE Singapore focusing on Digital Wellbeing. The project is funded by IMDA under the Digital for Life Initiative and operates at the national level.</p><p>The successful candidate(s) will support the delivery of this community project in areas such as community outreach and logistics and may be groomed to deliver talks to large audiences or conduct workshops and seminars.<br /></p><p><strong>Content Development</strong></p><p>-\tSupport development of content and materials for talks and seminars</p><p>-\tProvide insights into research and co-develop strategies for effective engagement of the different age groups.</p><p>-\tSupport creation of materials for training of volunteer leaders via TTT</p><p><br /><strong>Partnerships</strong></p><p>-\tProvide support for outreach activities to Schools and IHLs.</p><p>-\tManage mailings and event preparation for activities planned for Schools and IHLs, or volunteers</p><p><strong>Administration</strong></p><p>-\tResponsible for the collation of data and information for timely reporting to IMDA based on reporting requirements</p><p>-\tSupport the team to ensure that name lists of attendees and data needed for any other supporting documents are captured and stored securely.</p><p>-\tManage and maintain a database of members who sign up</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>-\tDiploma/Degree</p><p>-\t2 years of working experience in managing projects or volunteers preferred</p><p>-\tInterest in supporting the mental wellness of young people.</p><p>-\tPossess good interpersonal and communication skills (written and oral)<br /></p><p>* Only short-listed candidates will be contacted for an interview</p>",
